00:47:35.640 --> 00:47:41.070
And in 1997, I finally got around
to interviewing Charles Schultz

00:47:41.070 --> 00:47:43.430
for the Comics Journal.

00:47:43.430 --> 00:47:45.250
I decided, you know, it was time.

00:47:45.250 --> 00:47:49.020
I met Charles Schultz in 19 I
think -- or 1987, where I --

00:47:49.020 --> 00:47:51.680
I was a junior partner
